<!-- Intoriduction -->
	<purpose>
	<p>
	This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the identification of the shape of an object and portions of that shape and to characterize with properties a shape or shape portion.
	</p>

<!-- 2nd edition -->	
<p>   
The second edition of this part of ISO 10303 included the modifications to the first edition listed below.
</p>
	<p>The following ARM EXPRESS declarations have been split off into the new module <b>characterizable_object</b>:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Characterizable_object.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
	For upward compatibility they are included into this module by a USE FROM declaration.
	In addition, modifications have been made to the mapping specification, 
	the MIM schema and the EXPRESS-G diagrams to reflect and be consistent with the modifications of the ARM.
	</p>
	
	<!-- ARM changes -->
	<p>The following ARM EXPRESS data types have been modified:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Shape_element;</li>
		<li>Shape_element_relationship.</li>
	</ul>
	
<!-- 3rd edition -->
<p>   
